+# PR-214 Remediation Report
+
+## Thread Triage
+
+- `T-214-01`: actionable
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate of `T-214-01`
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete outdated hunk
+- `T-214-04`: actionable
+- `T-214-05`: actionable
+
+The authoritative classification is recorded in `artifacts/review/thread_triage.json` from `.github/review_export/pr_214_threads.json`.
+
+## Code Remediation
+
+Updated `src/policy/approval_router.py` so `build_policy_preview(...)` always passes `normalize_approval_state(...)` into the preview builder. This preserves the `manual_review` to `human_review_required` normalization on both live-preview and fallback paths.
+
+Updated `src/policy/preview.py` so the fallback payload keeps:
+
+- `approval_state`
+- `requires_human_review`
+
+This corrects the reopened regression where `preview_enabled=False` dropped the human-review signal from the payload.
+
+## Test Coverage
+
+Updated `tests/test_preview.py` to:
+
+- assert the fallback payload retains `approval_state="human_review_required"`
+- assert the fallback payload retains `requires_human_review=true`
+- add a regression for `build_policy_preview(..., approval_state="manual_review", preview_enabled=False, ...)`
+
+`tests/test_approval_router.py` was left unchanged as required.
+
+## Docs
+
+Updated `docs/approval_policy.md` so the fallback response example now shows:
+
+```json
+{
+  "request_id": "req-214",
+  "status": "preview_unavailable",
+  "actor": "review-bot",
+  "approval_state": "human_review_required",
+  "requires_human_review": true
+}
+```
+
+## Verification
+
+Executed:
+
+```bash
+python3 -m unittest tests.test_preview tests.test_approval_router
+```
+
+Result: `Ran 5 tests ... OK`
