+
+### T-214-01
+
+Fixed in `src/policy/preview.py`. The fallback payload now keeps both `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` instead of dropping them when `preview_enabled=False`.
+
+### T-214-02
+
+Handled as a duplicate of `T-214-01`. No separate code change was needed because the reopened fallback regression was fixed once in `src/policy/preview.py`.
+
+### T-214-03
+
+Not applied. This thread points at an outdated hunk in `src/policy/approval_router.py`, and I did not revive any legacy preview branch behavior on the current branch.
+
+### T-214-04
+
+Covered in `tests/test_preview.py`. Added a regression that exercises `build_policy_preview(..., approval_state="manual_review", preview_enabled=False, ...)` and asserts the normalized fallback payload still returns `approval_state="human_review_required"` with `requires_human_review=true`.
+
+### T-214-05
+
+Updated `docs/approval_policy.md` so the fallback example matches the corrected payload and includes `approval_state` plus `requires_human_review`.
